article.headline: Napper scores 19, Longwood ups win streak to 12 with 68-49 victory over VMI
article.description: — Walyn Napper scored 19 points as Longwood notched its 12th straight victory, beating VMI 68-49 on Sunday.
article.linkText: Napper scores 19, Longwood ups win streak to 12 with 68-49 victory over VMI

article.story: FARMVILLE, Va. -- — Walyn Napper scored 19 points as Longwood notched its 12th straight victory, beating VMI 68-49 on Sunday. Napper added five steals for the Lancers (12-1). Szymon Zapala scored 15 points and added five rebounds. Johnathan Massie shot 6 for 17 (0 for 5 from 3-point range) and 0 of 4 from the free throw line to finish with 12 points. Tyran Cook finished with 14 points for the Keydets (2-10). Devin Butler added 12 points for VMI. Koree Cotton also had nine points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
